This package allows me to interact with my data using natural language.

00:11:07.320 --> 00:11:10.520
It provides the UI scaffolding for that.

00:11:10.520 --> 00:11:13.440
The second one is ChatList.

00:11:13.440 --> 00:11:18.080
This really abstracts away the complexity of connecting to LLMs.

00:11:18.080 --> 00:11:23.559
So here you can see I'm connecting to Snowflake Cortex and using the Cloud for Solid model.

00:11:23.640 --> 00:11:24.640
All right.

00:11:24.640 --> 00:11:29.039
So let's see how this app, the Shiny for Python app, is doing.

00:11:29.039 --> 00:11:35.640
We'll run it within PostgreSQL.

00:11:35.640 --> 00:11:42.039
This is what QueryChat allows me to do, ask these natural language questions to this dashboard.

00:11:42.039 --> 00:11:46.400
And I can ask something like show states only on the West Coast.

00:11:46.400 --> 00:11:51.840
At the back end, it's going to leverage Cortex to do this text to SQL and then update my

00:11:51.840 --> 00:11:56.960
dashboard, which is pulling data from the Lending Club database automatically.

00:11:56.960 --> 00:12:05.080
So I see the dashboard has been updated.

00:12:05.080 --> 00:12:10.559
If I go into state analysis, I just see those three states, which is associating with the

00:12:10.559 --> 00:12:11.559
West Coast.

00:12:11.559 --> 00:12:12.559
So this is good.

00:12:12.559 --> 00:12:18.520
Now, let's say at this time, a stakeholder just asks me to see a simple table of default

00:12:18.520 --> 00:12:21.479
rate by state within the dashboard.

